U.S. Court of Appeals Issues Nationwide Stay on EPA “Waters of the US” Rule
The U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit issued a nationwide stay on water regulations created by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, commonly
referred to as the “Waters of the U.S.” or “WOTUS” rule in May, 2015. The rule would expand the jurisdiction of the EPA in regulating certain bodies of water and wetlands under the Clean Water
Act.
