IX Power Advisory Board
IX Power  is pleased to announce  the Company has formed an Advisory Board whose distinguished members represent a very high level of expertise in all of the technology segments that have a strong relationship to IX Power’s product lines and future developments. The members will assist the management team in a variety of ways, including assessment of technology options, development of new technologies, and utilization of breakthrough innovations. The contributions of the team will play an important role in IX Power’s mission of becoming a leading provider of safe power and clean water solutions for use in community, industry, government, and military applications.
IX Power LLC is privileged to have the following esteemed industry leaders on its Advisory Board
Mr. Alun Cole, Esq. Advisory Board, IX Power
Mr. Alun Cole, Esq.—IX Power Advisory Board ChairmanSolicitor of the Senior Courts of England and WalesMr. Cole is a highly regarded attorney with extensive experience in international capital development.  He is currently the CEO of Africa Capital Developments, which is focused on creating and implementing affordable and sustainable healthcare solutions in sub-Sahara Africa. Mr. Cole has degrees from the London School of Economics and is active on numerous community and industry committees.
 
 
Carol Bell, Ph.D.Oil & Gas Industry ExecutiveDr. Carol Bell has over 30 years’ experience in the oil and gas sector. She began her career in corporate planning and business development in the exploration and production sector at Charterhouse Petroleum and RTZ Oil & Gas. Following this, Dr. Bell enjoyed a successful career in investment banking as a Managing Director of Chase Manhattan Bank’s Global Oil & Gas Group, Head of European Equity Research at JP Morgan and several years as an equity research analyst in the oil and gas sector at Credit Suisse First Boston and UBS Phillips & Drew.  She is currently a non-executive director of the exploration and production companies Salamander Energy plc and Det norske oljeselskap ASA as well as at the seismic contractor PGS ASA. Dr. Bell is also a Trustee of the Renewable Energy Foundation and chairs the Investment Committee of Girton College, Cambridge. She was awarded a Ph.D. in the archaeology of ancient trade in May 2005 and continues her research in this area at University College London.  
Robert Bednarz, PhD, Advisory Board, IX Power
Robert Bednarz, Ph.D.Professor, Texas A&M UniversityDr. Robert Bednarz is a recognized global expert in economic geography.  A professor at Texas A & M University whose main academic interests fall into two areas, geographic education and urban-economic geography, he has written eight books and countless articles.   Over the past 15 years, during which he served as editor of the Journal of Geography and now as North American editor of the Journal of Geography in Higher Education, Dr. Bednarz is focused mainly on topics related to how people learn, organize, and use geographic information. His research interests lie within the broad area of spatial thinking, especially in how information technology (IT) affects individuals’ ability to perceive, understand, and analyze spatial patterns, distributions, and relationships. Dr. Bednarz has served on several boards including the advisory board to Hyperion Power Generation.  He holds degrees from Dartmouth College and Northwestern University. His Ph.D. was obtained from the University of Chicago.
Mr. Michael Crawford, Advisory Board, IX Power
Mr. Michael CrawfordPartner, Q AdvisorsMichael Crawford has over 20 years of investment banking and operating experience. During his investment-banking career, Michael has executed mergers and acquisitions and raised equity and debt capital through both private placements and public offerings. Michael has worked with companies in a range of industries including telecommunications, software, alternative energy, consumer products and manufacturing. Noteworthy clients include Bolo Systems, Narus, Summit Doppler, Switch Communications, and WVT Communications.  Michael is on the Board of the Colorado Youth Soccer and has served on the Board of Directors of the Parkinson Association of the Rockies and ArtReach, two non-profit organizations in Denver. Michael received a B.A. in Economics from Lafayette College and an M.B.A. from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania.



















